eecalcs.conductors

Class PropertySet

  • java.lang.Object
    • eecalcs.conductors.PropertySet

  • public class PropertySet
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates a set of all the electrical properties of a conductor as defined in NEC 2014 tables 310.15(B)(16), 8 and 9

      • PropertySet

        public PropertySet(java.lang.String size,
                   int CuAmp60,
                   int CuAmp75,
                   int CuAmp90,
                   int AlAmp60,
                   int AlAmp75,
                   int AlAmp90,
                   double nonMagXL,
                   double magXL,
                   double CuResInPVCCond,
                   double CuResInALCond,
                   double CuResInSteelCond,
                   double ALResInPVCCond,
                   double ALResInALCond,
                   double ALResInSteelCond,
                   int areaCM,
                   double CuResDCUncoated,
                   double CuResDCCoated,
                   double ALResDC)
        Constructs a PropertySet object. This constructor is used by the class CondProp to populate its internal table with data for all recognized conductor sizes as per table NEC 2014 310.15(B)(16), providing a set of electrical properties for each conductor size. It should not be used unless the user wants to build a special conductor (non listed in the NEC table). The constructor also constructs the associated CopperProp and AluminumProp. AluminumProp objects that encapsulate the correspondent properties according to the conductor metal type (copper or aluminum)
        Parameters:
        size - The size of this conductor as defined by Size
        CuAmp60 - The ampacity of this copper conductor with an insulation rated for 60°C
        CuAmp75 - The ampacity of this copper conductor with an insulation rated for 75°C
        CuAmp90 - The ampacity of this copper conductor with an insulation rated for 90°C
        AlAmp60 - The ampacity of this aluminum conductor with an insulation rated for 60°C
        AlAmp75 - The ampacity of this aluminum conductor with an insulation rated for 75°C
        AlAmp90 - The ampacity of this aluminum conductor with an insulation rated for 90°C
        nonMagXL - The inductive reactance of this conductor when used in a non magnetic conduit
        magXL - The inductive reactance of this conductor when used in a magnetic conduit
        CuResInPVCCond - The AC resistance of this copper conductor when used in a PVC conduit
        CuResInALCond - The AC resistance of this copper conductor when used in an aluminum conduit
        CuResInSteelCond - The AC resistance of this copper conductor when used in a steel conduit
        ALResInPVCCond - The AC resistance of this aluminum conductor when used in a PVC conduit
        ALResInALCond - The AC resistance of this aluminum conductor when used in an aluminum conduit
        ALResInSteelCond - The AC resistance of this aluminum conductor when used in a steel conduit
        areaCM - The area in Circular Mil of this conductor
        CuResDCUncoated - The DC resistance of this uncoated copper conductor
        CuResDCCoated - The DC resistance of this coated copper conductor
        ALResDC - The DC resistance of this aluminum conductor

      • getDCResistance

        public double getDCResistance(Metal metal,
                              double length,
                              int numberOfSets,
                              boolean copperCoated)
        Returns the DC resistance of this conductor size for the given metal, length, sets, etc. If the specified metal is aluminum, the copperCoated parameter is ignored.
        Parameters:
        metal - The metal of the conductor.
        length - The length of the conductor.
        numberOfSets - The number of conductors in parallel.
        copperCoated - Indicates for a copper conductor if it is coated or not.
        Returns:
        The DC resistance in ohms of this conductor size under the given conditions.

      • getDCResistance
